## map_tile.lsl — add SHUTDOWN listener for board rez

Current `on_rez` guard (line 222):
```lsl
if (start_param == 0) return;  // rezzed from inventory — stay inert
```

Change to:
```lsl
if (start_param == 0)
{
    // Rezzed as part of the linked MapBoard — stay visually inert
    // but listen for SHUTDOWN so the controller can clean up the board.
    llListen(MAP_TILE, "", NULL_KEY, "SHUTDOWN");
    return;
}
```

The existing `if (cmd == "SHUTDOWN") { llDie(); return; }` handler in the MAP_TILE listen block already handles this; calling `llDie()` from the root prim kills the entire linkset.

The controller sends `llRegionSayTo(gBoard_Key, MAP_TILE, "SHUTDOWN")` — targeted to root prim only, which calls `llDie()` on behalf of the whole board.

